AUDIO: 'What is this thing? Is it a camera, a gadget, or something completely different? Because this tiny device has been recording my life quietly for the past 2 days. Definitely is not built for perfect high-resolution shots. It\'s actually designed to understand your'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'life more like [music] a second brain. This is the Louie L1, and it might be one of the most interesting AI gadgets I\'ve tested this year. Louie isn\'t trying to replace your phone. It\'s not even trying to be a camera. Instead,'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it\'s designed to support your life almost like something that\'s [music] taking alongside you. The reason that matters is because most of us go through our day on autopilot. We miss things not because they\'re not there, but because'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'our brain can [music] only process so much at once. Louie acts like a third eye, quietly observing everything in the background. It records small moments throughout your day, then turns that into something way more interesting,'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which are called life logs, insights, daily vlogs, even comics out of your life. And personally, the comics stood out to me the most because it\'s not just showing me what I did. It\'s showing my'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'patterns, moments in my life, things I didn\'t even realize were part of my day. Louie has this feature called AI story mode. Once it\'s on, you literally forget about it. You don\'t have to think about'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'recording. [music] It automatically captures and analyzes the key moments in your day-to-day life without you having to do anything. It just captures moment every couple of minutes in the background like a silent observer, tracking your day without interrupting'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it. You can ask it things like a real person, and it talks back to you. Not in like a robotic way, but more like a companion. Hey Louie, what is your purpose? &gt;&gt; My purpose is to support you, helping'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'capture and reflect on your moments, keeping you organized with reminders, and being a companion you can rely on both creatively and in daily life. &gt;&gt; And by the end of the day, it gives you'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everything back in [music] a completely different way. I think really that\'s the point of Loqui. It\'s not about capturing perfect moments, it\'s about capturing real ones because [music] you start noticing things you\'re normally ignoring. Little routines, conversations'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here [music] and there, moments that would have been forgotten. The more I wear Loqui, the more it gets to know me. Another feature that I like is the pie feature, Loqui pie. Before I headed out'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to film today for my session, I told Loqui to basically be my [music] assistant, like look out for interesting things that I\'m doing. If I could improve on anything, just let me know. During my filming outside, it was about'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to rain and it predicted it was going to rain and it [music] was telling me what angles to get and it\'s telling me I got about 90 minutes left of light, [music] which is something I appreciate as a videographer. An assistant looking out for me while I film, this little device'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is powerful. Now, that being said, here\'s what I think they can improve on. The real life comics, although they show my routine and [music] environment pretty well, they did capture my feature as well the first time I wore it. After'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that, my character started looking like a different person for each new comic. And second, this might be me nitpicking, but if there were a way to edit the daily vlogs it gives you at the end of each day, like adjusting the text on'

